  "display_name": "Law in Society and Culture",
  "description": "This cluster of papers explores the intersection of visual representation, semiotics, and jurisprudence, with a focus on courtroom design, the use of imagery in law and film, the portrayal of affect and emotion in legal proceedings, and the cultural diplomacy of legal art. It delves into topics such as transitional justice, human rights in art, and the ethics of courtroom imagery, offering a multidisciplinary perspective on the visual aspects of law and justice.",
